1 (III) WILL BEST MAINTAIN HISTORICAL, ENVIRONMENTAL, OR
2 AGRICULTURAL PRESERVATION AREAS; OR
3 (IV) WILL AVOID ANY OVERLAP WITH A LOT, PARCEL, OR TRACT
4 OF LAND THAT IS:
5 1. LOCATED WITHIN A PLANNED GROWTH AREA
6 IDENTIFIED IN THE LOCAL JURISDICTION’S COMPREHENSIVE PLAN; OR
7 2. ZONED FOR RESIDENTIAL USE OR MIXED USE WITH A
8 RESIDENTIAL COMPONENT.
9 (2) ALTERNATIVES TO THE CONSTRUCTION OF A NEW TRANSMISSION
10 LINE INCLUDE:
11 (I) THE USE OF AN EXISTING TRANSMISSION LINE OF ANOTHER
12 COMPANY;
13 (II) THE USE OF AN EXISTING RIGHT–OF–WAY;
14 (III) RECONDUCTORING AN EXISTING TRANSMISSION LINE; AND
15 (IV) UNDERGROUNDING A TRANSMISSION LINE.
16 (b) In considering the use of an [existing transmission line] ALTERNATIVE under
17 subsection (a) of this section, the Commission need not consider whether the company that
18 owns the line has a franchise in a service area.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
20 October 1, 2025.

